@startuml audio_focus_to_amp_ducking_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Audio Focus To AMP Ducking Signal Flow\n(audio focus / TTS / media state -> AMP ducking and render volume)

participant "Media / audio-focus /\nvoice context" as AudioCtx #F4F7FB
participant "AMP\naudio output owner" as AMP #E8F7E8
participant "AMP state / UiRender" as AmpBus #FFF4CC
participant "Observers / audio users" as Obs #E8F0FE

== Audio Inputs ==

AudioCtx -> AMP : mediaState / muteState / volumeLevel\naudioFocusOwner / audioDuckingLvl\nvoiceAssistState / ttsState
AMP -> AMP : baseVolume = deriveBaseVolume(Inject::alertVolumeCmd)
AMP -> AMP : ampMode from media / voice / tts activity
AMP -> AMP : ampDucking escalates when TTS / voice / focus is active
AMP -> AMP : if volume >= 90 or ducking >= 6\nthen raise ducking and force voice-safe mode
note right of AMP
Representative gating inputs
- audioFocusOwner / audioDuckingLvl
- voiceAssistState / ttsState
- mediaState / volumeLevel
end note

== AMP Publish ==

AMP -> AmpBus : frmAmpStateMsg\nAmpMode / AmpMute / AmpDuckingLvl / AmpVolumeLevel
AMP -> AmpBus : UiRender::renderVolumLevel
note right of AMP
Representative outputs
- AmpMode
- AmpDuckingLvl
- AmpVolumeLevel
- renderVolumLevel
end note

== Downstream Visibility ==

AmpBus -> Obs : audio-output readback /\nrender-volume consumers

note over AudioCtx, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. Media, focus, and speech context reach AMP
2. AMP decides ducking level and output mode
3. AMP publishes audio state and render volume
4. Observers expose the effective audio priority posture
end note

@enduml
